1. From a  historycal perspective, societal beauty standards and cultural norms around body shape and size have evolved over time, often perpetuating negative attitudes towards overweight individuals;
2. From a  real social perspective, stigma, discrimination, and social exclusion can lead to feelings of shame, low self-esteem, and social isolation;
3. From  anthropology, biological, and psychological    perspectives, internalized negative self-talk, body dissatisfaction, and emotional distress can also contribute to increased self-awareness and  social challenges for individuals who are overweight or obese."
